{quote}How about we still fix this in trunk, but mark it as incompatible?
{quote}
This seems reasonable. We can go ahead with trunk fix.

Hi [~vinayrpet] and [~ayushtkn], thanks for reporting and working on it.  The overall idea LGTM.  Just have two comments, one is a new exception class 

NoECPolicySetException seems a little heavy. It's not a Hadoop tradition to create a new exception for each specific error reason.  Another is the error message 
{code:java}
+    } else {
+      throw new NoECPolicySetException(
+          "No erasure coding policy explicitly set on " + src
+              + ". Use -setPolicy -path <PATH> -replicate to enforce "
+              + "default replication policy irresptive of EC policy"
+              + " defined on parent");{code}
The message is thrown by the NN and it carries the information of an command tool format.  Usually it's better not include external tool info in NN. .

